mg:name
        rdf:type          owl:DatatypeProperty;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "name";
        rdfs:comment      "Capitalized string identifier of an Entity as extracted by the LLM from a text chunk, used for exact-match deduplication across extraction instances (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.2: 'entity name: Name of the entity, capitalized'; Appendix A.1: 'identifies all entities … including their name, type, and description')."@en,
                          "Identifiant textuel capitalisé d'une Entité tel qu'extrait par le LLM à partir d'un fragment textuel, utilisé pour la déduplication par correspondance exacte entre instances d'extraction (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.2 : « entity name: Name of the entity, capitalized » ; Annexe A.1 : « identifies all entities … including their name, type, and description »)."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:28:39.603Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:28:39.603Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:text
        rdf:type          owl:DatatypeProperty;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "text";
        rdfs:comment      "Raw string content of a Chunk as it appears after document splitting, passed verbatim to the LLM for entity and relationship extraction (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1, Appendix E.1: 'Given a text document … identify all entities of those types from the text')."@en,
                          "Contenu textuel brut d'un Chunk tel qu'il apparaît après découpage du document, transmis tel quel au LLM pour l'extraction d'entités et de relations (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1, Annexe E.1 : « Given a text document … identify all entities of those types from the text »)."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:26:51.923Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:26:51.923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:EntityShape
        rdf:type        sh:NodeShape;
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:id
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:name
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:class  mg:Community;
                          sh:path   mg:inCommunity
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:description
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:class  mg:Entity;
                          sh:path   mg:relatedTo
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:humanReadableId
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:descriptionEmbedding
                        ];
        sh:targetClass  mg:Entity .

mg:Entity
        rdf:type          owl:Class;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "Entity"@en, "Entité"@fr;
        rdfs:comment      "A named concept (person, place, organization, etc.) extracted by the LLM from a text chunk; becomes a node in the knowledge graph with a name, type and aggregated description (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.2: 'the LLM is prompted to extract instances of important entities … the broad class of named entities like people, places, and organizations')."@en,
                          "Concept nommé (personne, lieu, organisation, etc.) extrait par le LLM à partir d'un fragment textuel ; devient un nœud du graphe de connaissances doté d'un nom, d'un type et d'une description agrégée (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.2 : « the LLM is prompted to extract instances of important entities … the broad class of named entities like people, places, and organizations »)."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:26:29.280Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:36:26.557Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:ChunkShape
        rdf:type        sh:NodeShape;
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:text
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:class  mg:Entity;
                          sh:path   mg:hasEntity
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:id
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:class  mg:Covariate;
                          sh:path   mg:hasCovariate
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:class     mg:Document;
                          sh:minCount  1;
                          sh:path      mg:partOf
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:integer;
                          sh:path      mg:nTokens
                        ];
        sh:targetClass  mg:Chunk .

mg:Chunk
        rdf:type          owl:Class;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "Chunk"@en, "Fragment textuel"@fr;
        rdfs:comment      "A fixed-size, overlapping sub-segment of a Document used as the LLM extraction unit (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1: 'the documents in the corpus are split into text chunks … 600-token text chunks, with 100-token overlaps'). The LLM extracts entities, relationships and claims from each chunk."@en,
                          "Sous-segment de Document de taille fixe avec chevauchement, utilisé comme unité d'extraction par le LLM (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1 : « the documents in the corpus are split into text chunks … 600-token text chunks, with 100-token overlaps »). Le LLM extrait entités, relations et revendications à partir de chaque fragment."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:24:39.607Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-16T05:54:10.447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:nTokens
        rdf:type          owl:DatatypeProperty;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "n_tokens";
        rdfs:comment      "Number of LLM tokens in a Chunk or summary text, used to enforce context-window limits during community summarization (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1: '600-token text chunks'; §3.1.5: 'rank sub-communities in decreasing order of element summary tokens'). Not named in the paper; field name is from the GraphRAG open-source implementation."@en,
                          "Nombre de tokens LLM dans un Chunk ou un texte de résumé, utilisé pour respecter les limites de fenêtre de contexte lors de la synthèse des communautés (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1 : « 600-token text chunks » ; §3.1.5 : « rank sub-communities in decreasing order of element summary tokens »). Le nom de champ n'apparaît pas dans l'article ; il provient de l'implémentation open-source de GraphRAG."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:24:39.607Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:24:39.607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:id
        rdf:type          owl:DatatypeProperty;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "id";
        rdfs:comment      "Unique identifier of a graph element (entity, relationship, claim, community) used in data provenance references within community reports (arXiv:2404.16130v2, Appendix E.2: 'the id (not the index) of the relevant data record'). The paper consistently distinguishes the id from positional index."@en,
                          "Identifiant unique d'un élément du graphe (entité, relation, revendication, communauté) utilisé dans les références de provenance des données au sein des rapports de communauté (arXiv:2404.16130v2, Annexe E.2 : « the id (not the index) of the relevant data record »). L'article distingue systématiquement l'id de l'index positionnel."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:22:48.036Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:22:48.036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:DocumentShape
        rdf:type        sh:NodeShape;
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:title
                        ];
        sh:property     [ sh:datatype  xsd:string;
                          sh:path      mg:id
                        ];
        sh:targetClass  mg:Document .

mg:Document
        rdf:type          owl:Class;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "Document"@en, "Document"@fr;
        rdfs:comment      "A source text record in the private corpus used as input to the GraphRAG pipeline (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1: 'the documents in the corpus are split into text chunks'). Documents are split into fixed-size Chunks before LLM processing."@en,
                          "Un enregistrement de texte source du corpus privé utilisé comme entrée du pipeline GraphRAG (arXiv:2404.16130v2, §3.1.1 : « the documents in the corpus are split into text chunks »). Les documents sont découpés en Chunks de taille fixe avant traitement par le LLM."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:21:45.753Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:22:48.036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

mg:title
        rdf:type          owl:DatatypeProperty;
        rdfs:isDefinedBy  mg:;
        rdfs:label        "title";
        rdfs:comment      "Short, specific human-readable name of a CommunityReport assigned by the LLM, intended to include representative named entities (arXiv:2404.16130v2, Appendix E.2: 'TITLE: community\'s name that represents its key entities — title should be short but specific')."@en,
                          "Nom humainement lisible, court et spécifique, d'un CommunityReport attribué par le LLM ; il doit inclure si possible des entités nommées représentatives (arXiv:2404.16130v2, Annexe E.2 : « TITLE: community's name that represents its key entities — title should be short but specific »)."@fr;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:contributor   "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:created       "2024-08-06T06:21:45.753Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dct:creator       "Ian Ormesher";
        dct:modified      "2024-08-06T06:21:45.753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

<http://ormynet.com/ns/msft-graphrag>
        rdf:type         owl:Ontology;
        rdfs:label       "Microsoft GraphRAG"@en, "Microsoft GraphRAG"@fr;
        rdfs:comment     "OWL ontology modelling the output schema of the Microsoft GraphRAG pipeline, as described in 'From Local to Global: A GraphRAG Approach to Query-Focused Summarization' (Edge et al., arXiv:2404.16130v2, 2024). The ontology captures the six core entity types produced by the pipeline — Document, Chunk, Entity, Community, Covariate, Finding — together with their properties and SHACL shapes. Terms grounded in the paper are annotated with section references; terms from the open-source implementation (https://github.com/microsoft/graphrag) are noted accordingly."@en,
                         "Ontologie OWL modélisant le schéma de sortie du pipeline Microsoft GraphRAG, tel que décrit dans « From Local to Global: A GraphRAG Approach to Query-Focused Summarization » (Edge et al., arXiv:2404.16130v2, 2024). L'ontologie représente les six types d'entités principaux produits par le pipeline — Document, Chunk, Entity, Community, Covariate, Finding — ainsi que leurs propriétés et leurs formes SHACL. Les termes ancrés dans l'article sont annotés avec leurs références de section ; les termes provenant de l'implémentation open-source (https://github.com/microsoft/graphrag) sont signalés comme tels."@fr;
        dct:source       <https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.16130>;
        <http://open-services.net/ns/core#modifiedBy>
                "Ian Ormesher";
